  • How do I buy Ondo Finance (ONDO)?
    Buying Ondo Finance (ONDO) in MetaMask wallet is speedy, simple, and safe. You can buy Ondo Finance (ONDO) tokens directly in MetaMask using payment methods like a credit card, debit card, bank account, Apple Pay, Google Pay, or PayPal. There's no need for centralised exchanges. Select from thousands of your favourite tokens to buy on over 15 networks including Ethereum, Solana, Linea, Base, and more.
  • What is Ondo Finance (ONDO) price history?
    Ondo Finance (ONDO) launched in 2020. Today, 8 September 2025, the price of Ondo Finance (ONDO) is $0.94. The all-time high of Ondo Finance (ONDO) is $2.14. The all-time low of Ondo Finance (ONDO) is $0.08. Ondo Finance's market capitalisation is $2,978,217,424.00.
  • What is the Ondo Finance (ONDO) price today?
    Today, 8 September 2025, the price of Ondo Finance (ONDO) is $0.94.
  • What is the Ondo Finance (ONDO) all-time high?
    The all-time high of Ondo Finance (ONDO) is $2.14.
  • What is the Ondo Finance (ONDO) all-time low?
    The all-time low of Ondo Finance (ONDO) is $0.08.
  • How do I sell Ondo Finance (ONDO)?
    MetaMask makes it easy to sell your Ondo Finance (ONDO) and convert your crypto to cash. You can exchange from MetaMask wallet directly to your debit card, credit card, PayPal, or bank account. By removing unnecessary steps and cutting excess fees, offramping your digital assets is fast and simple.
  • How do I swap Ondo Finance (ONDO)?
    Swapping ONDO is simple and cost-effective with MetaMask. Choose from thousands of your favourite tokens across ten networks including Ethereum, Solana, Linea, Base, and Arbitrum. MetaMask Swaps also include gas fees right in your quotes, making swapping crypto as smooth as can be.
  • How do I bridge Ondo Finance (ONDO)?
    Bridging crypto across chains allows you to move tokens from one network to another. With MetaMask, bridging Ondo Finance (ONDO) is easy, secure, and cost-effective. Our aggregator finds the most efficient routes to move your digital assets from one chain to another. And with cross-chain swapping, bridging and swapping can take place at the same time in a single transaction. Meaning: instead of bridging one token from chain A and wrapping or unwrapping it on chain B, you can swap one token from chain A to a second token on chain B, all in one move.
  • What can you do with Ondo Finance (ONDO)?
    With Ondo Finance, you can send and receive ONDO, the network's native token, and use it to pay transaction fees on certain networks. ONDO is supported in decentralised apps for trading, staking, payments, and NFTs. You can participate in DeFi protocols, bridge assets between networks, or use ONDO in select web3 games and marketplaces, all with Ethereum-compatible speed and flexibility.
  • How do I trade Ondo Finance for other cryptocurrencies?
    Trading ONDO for ETH, WBTC, or SOL can be done directly in MetaMask. For more information on how to swap ONDO, head to MetaMask Support's ONDO Integration.
